reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An interesting story
reviews.reviewText: This story has a Duke with a reputation that he’s has ruined several ladies. But Alicia gets involved when her friend is one of these ladies. But after she confronts him they realize that not is all that it seems. Will they figure out what’s going on especially as they get closer! I voluntarily reviewed an Advance Reader Copy of this book.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This story proves that you should not judge someone by the rumors that they hear. It's great how they work together to get to the truth of everything that happened. This story has a lot going on before they ever get to their happily ever after. Another wonderful book by Ms. Linfield that is a must read.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Dominic's reputation is horrible. Alicia is set on preventing anyone else from being hurt. Together they find that not everything is as it seems. A twisty engaging story that keeps you on your feet and fully engaged in the story. Lots of additional characters of interest making this story much more engaging to read.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Hatred turns to Love
reviews.reviewText: Dominic and his efforts to help other soon is plagued by a dishonest Earl and his daughter who is under his thumb. Alicia soon learns of the Dukes attempts to help others and her hatred turns to affection. The story of how this is resolved is enjoyableTo read and I really like this book and the characters

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Alicia has to change her opinion on the duke after she realizes the truth behind all the rumors about him. What was her opinion and what occurred to have her change it? How do they find their hea? All is revealed in this sweet and clean read. Some parts of the were a bit out of line with the conventions of that period but overall a sweet read

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Is the Duke a Rake?
reviews.reviewText: The Duke is known for ruining several ladies of the ton. His reputation always seems to come our alright until he meets his match in Alicia when he ruins her friend. The story has multiple character and twists throughout. Story keeps you guessing and holds your attention. I enjoyed the story and would recommend it.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars especially enjoyable beginning to end!
reviews.reviewText: First few pages I wasn’t sure how I’d enjoy the characters. But soon I was totally immersed in the story and it’s twist ,turns and carrying about the characters and their futures ! enjoyed it immensely!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Her Despicable Duke:
reviews.reviewText: I am really enjoying this book. It is well thought out and Emma brings you to the story. Well written with well rounded characters. I am not quite finished with it yet. I'm sure there are more surprises to come. But I do recommend it. Not your usual read so far.

reviews.reviewTitle: A charming enemies to lovers story
reviews.reviewText: An entertaining, sweet and clean romance with very likeable characters and a touch of intrigue.I loved how their relationship evolved from haters to allies to lovers and how the characters developed as the story progressed. Their verbal sparring and playful banter was enjoyable to read.Alicia and her family are still suffering from the scandal her older sister brought upon them last season. Her worst enemy is Duke Dominic, the man who presumably ruined her sister and who seems to enjoy taunting her at every opportunity.Dominic is fascinated by Alicia because she is different from the rest of society. She is daring and does not hesitate to show him her wrath.But when it seems that he has also ruined Alicia's best friend, she realises that all is not as it seems and that he may not be the villain she thought he was...If you like sweet and clean enemies to lovers historical romances, you will enjoy this story.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: Don't Judge a Duke by his Reputation
reviews.reviewText: This is an enjoyable read. The characters are very believable and I enjoyed the banter between Dominic and Alicia. I felt that Dominic was badly treated but eventually the truth was revealed and Alicia helped him to find the proof he needed to restore his reputation. A well-written story.
